Hello,

I think your problem stems from the fact that you&#39;re dealing with two different regexes, because of the different contexts in which your regex string appears. In java code &quot;&#92;&#92;?&quot; denotes &#92;? which matches a literal question mark. But in xml, &#92;&#92;? means &#92;&#92;?. In the regex that will mean, match 0 or 1 backslash (and no question marks).

In other words, you have two many backslashes in your regex in crawler-beans.cxml. I think the fix is to change it to
([a-zA-Z//:.&#92;&#92;]+index.php&#92;?start=[0-9]+)

As a side note you don&#39;t need or want the surrounding parens, and there&#39;s some other oddness in the regex. I&#39;d  suggest this instead: .*index&#92;.php&#92;?start=[0-9]+

Noah


